-- Guangzhou Starts Restricting Car Traffic for Asian Games, Xinhua Reports
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-11-01T19:45:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-01/guangzhou-starts-restricting-car-traffic-for-asian-games-xinhua-reports.html
Guangzhou has started restricting car
traffic as part of efforts to reduce air pollution and traffic
congestion for the Asian Games, to be held in the city Nov. 12-
Nov. 27, Xinhua News Agency reported.  Vehicles with odd-number plates were barred from the city
streets yesterday, to be followed by even-numbered plates today,
Xinhua reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  